<div class="content-box" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
    <h2>A deliberately humble commitment</h2>
    <p>
        To be clear about what this page is and is not: it is <strong>not</strong> a claim that Web
        Everything will be adopted, standardized, or handed to a foundation. It is a commitment about
        <em>how</em> governance would evolve <em>if</em> the work proves useful to anyone beyond its
        author — and an honest statement that, today, it is one person's project, governed in the open.
    </p>
    <p>
        The transition between stages is driven by reality, not ambition. If adoption never comes,
        stage&nbsp;1 is where this stays — and that is a perfectly acceptable outcome for a project
        whose first job is simply to be useful and honest about itself.
    </p>
